cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV 

This paper is about analysing neural language models, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). The paper specifically focuses on syntactic agreement and co-reference resolution, which are sub-tasks within NLP. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also proposes a generalisation of Contextual Decomposition, which is a technique used in machine learning and deep learning, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely category. The paper also investigates the information that LSTMs base their decisions on, which is related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper uses LSTMs, which is a type of neural network, making cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) another possible category. Finally, the paper may also fall under cs.CV (Computer Vision) as co-reference resolution is a task that is also relevant in image and video analysis.
